latestPosts.caption:
It’s the first day of the iconic Venice carnival that we all sit in anticipation for every year 🎭❤️

The Venice Carnival (Carnevale di Venezia) is one of the most magical and historic carnivals in the world! Dating back to the 12th century, it was originally a time for people to wear masks and enjoy total freedom, blurring social classes in a grand celebration. Today, it’s a spectacle of art, tradition, and elegance. ❣️

Shoutout to @aniab @marino.gobita @elen.venezia @ig_adelle

latestPosts.caption:
4 Italy Travel Myths You Can Ignore👇✈️

1️⃣ “You can do Rome, Florence, Venice, and the Amalfi Coast in 10 days.” – It’s tempting, but Italy isn’t a race! Slow down and enjoy each destination without rushing.
2️⃣ “Every day should be fully planned.” – Nope! Leave room for spontaneous long lunches, detours, and hidden gems you didn’t expect to love.
3️⃣ “Always stay in big cities.” – While cities are iconic, the charm of Italy often lies in the smaller towns and countryside.
4️⃣ “The more places you visit, the better.” – Quality over quantity! Immerse yourself in each place instead of trying to see everything at once.

Tag someone who needs to enjoy Italy at a slower pace with you!❤️💫

latestPosts.caption:
The Venice of France is calling! Colmar’s picturesque canals and colorful houses are a dream come true. 🏡🩷

💡Colmar is a picturesque city in the Alsace region of northeastern France, known for its well-preserved old town, colorful half-timbered houses, and charming canals, earning it the nickname “Little Venice”. Colmar is a historic, culturally rich city famous for its medieval architecture, art museums, wine production, and vibrant festivals, making it a captivating destination in the Alsace region of France.

If Colmar is on your bucket list, drop a 💙 in the comments and tell us why you want to visit!

La Venise de France vous appelle ! Les canaux pittoresques et les maisons colorées de Colmar sont un véritable rêve devenu réalité. 🏡🩷

💡Colmar est une ville pittoresque située dans la région Alsace, dans le nord-est de la France, connue pour sa vieille ville bien préservée, ses maisons à colombages colorées et ses charmants canaux, ce qui lui vaut le surnom de « Petite Venise ». Colmar est une ville historique et culturellement riche, célèbre pour son architecture médiévale, ses musées d’art, sa production de vin et ses festivals animés, faisant d’elle une destination captivante en Alsace.

Si Colmar est sur votre liste de voyages, laissez un 💙 en commentaire et dites-nous pourquoi vous souhaitez visiter cette ville !
